<br>
I'm not sure I get the argument that he could not do this without others in the zone.  I mean, most of the really badass buffs he would want would be relatively long lasting, right?  He could get them anywhere.  If he is in such an uberguild, and has other ubertoons, he could just get the monkey buffed, ported to the zone, then camped inside the dungeon to preserve the buffs.  Then, all he had to do was get his own uber toon (or more if he had them, seems many ubers use two machines, right?) to clear the way to the dragon (seems if he could kill the dragon, he could kill the giants, but the time issue on the buffs might make that a bad idea).  Once giants are cleared, he moves his studly monkey to start the fight.<br>
<br>
Now, I am not an old world dragon expert, but isn't this a pretty easy explanation for how someone like that could get a max buffed toon to the dragon with most or all the time still left on the buffs, without needing anyone else in the zone to help?  If so, all you have to deal with is whether he can beat the dragon while fuly buffed and with no one else there to help.  Seems to me all he needs then is something to heal him.  I don't play any real melees, so I don't know what uber items are out there (clickies or potions or something) which would provide the healing he needed.  But I imagine there are some.<br>
<br>
I admit it sounds hard, but my hat is off to anyone who had the stones to try this and succeed.<br>
